## Technological Innovations

Technological advancements complement policy and behavioral changes.

- **Post-Combustion Controls:** Installation of scrubbers and catalytic converters in power plants and industries reduces SO2, NOx, and particulate emissions ([Climatetracker, 2018](https://climatetracker.org/25-solutions-to-air-pollution/)).
- **Electric and Hybrid Vehicles:** Adoption of EVs reduces tailpipe emissions and dependence on fossil fuels ([California Air Resources Board, 2011](https://ww2.arb.ca.gov/resources/fact-sheets/simple-solutions-help-reduce-air-pollution)).
- **Intelligent Transportation Systems (ITS):** Technologies that optimize traffic flow reduce congestion and emissions ([EPA, 1998](https://www.epa.gov/state-and-local-transportation/estimating-emission-reductions-travel-efficiency-strategies)).
- **Energy Efficiency Technologies:** Use of energy-efficient appliances, LED lighting, and improved building insulation reduce electricity demand and associated emissions ([California Air Resources Board, 2011](https://ww2.arb.ca.gov/resources/fact-sheets/simple-solutions-help-reduce-air-pollution)).

---

## Agricultural and Waste Management Strategies

- **Agricultural Practices:** Intermittent aeration in rice paddies reduces methane emissions; banning open burning of crop residues lowers particulate pollution ([Climatetracker, 2018](https://climatetracker.org/25-solutions-to-air-pollution/)).
- **Wastewater Treatment:** Biogas recovery from wastewater treatment plants reduces methane emissions ([Climatetracker, 2018](https://climatetracker.org/25-solutions-to-air-pollution/)).
- **Solid Waste Management:** Centralized waste collection with source separation and treatment prevents uncontrolled emissions ([Climatetracker, 2018](https://climatetracker.org/25-solutions-to-air-pollution/)).

