## Health and Environmental Benefits

Reducing air pollution yields immediate and long-term health benefits:

- **Respiratory Health:** Lower levels of PM, NOx, and VOCs reduce asthma attacks and respiratory illnesses ([California Air Resources Board, 2011](https://ww2.arb.ca.gov/resources/fact-sheets/simple-solutions-help-reduce-air-pollution)).
- **Climate Mitigation:** Decreasing emissions of greenhouse gases and short-lived climate pollutants contributes to climate change mitigation ([Center for Climate and Energy Solutions, 2008](https://www.c2es.org/document/policies-to-reduce-emissions-from-the-transportation-sector/)).
- **Economic Savings:** The UK government estimates air pollution reduction strategies could save society Â£1 billion annually by 2020, rising to Â£2.5 billion by 2030 ([UK Government, 2019](https://www.gov.uk/government/news/new-clean-air-strategy-to-be-launched-by-environment-secretary-michael-gove)).

